'''Herbert John Goodes''' {{post-nominals|country=AUS|CBE}} was a senior Australian public servant and policymaker.

==Life and career==
Goodes was born in England, migrating to Australia in the 1920s and reaching Western Australia where he took on casual work, including digging dams and fencing.<ref name=CTObit>{{cite news|url=http://nla.gov.au/nla.news-article118132988|newspaper=The Canberra Times|date=21 July 1986|page=8|title=Obituary: Mr Herbert Goodes Social-service planner}}</ref> In the 1930s, Goodes enrolled to study part-time at the [[University of Western Australia]], graduating with honours in economics.<ref name=CTObit/>

In 1939, Goodes married Joyce and together they moved to Canberra in 1943 when he was seconded to the [[Department of the Treasury (Australia)|Department of the Treasury]] from the WA Registry of Births, Deaths and Marriages.<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.womenaustralia.info/biogs/AWE4856b.htm|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130514074742/http://www.womenaustralia.info/biogs/AWE4856b.htm|archivedate=14 May 2013|title=Goodes, Joyce Nancy (1916 - 1990)|work=The Australian Women's Register|first1=Jayne|last1=Goodes|first2=Dinah|last2=Goodes}}</ref> 

Between 1958 and 1965, Goodes was the [[Departmental secretary|Secretary]] of the [[Department of Social Services (1939–1972)|Department of Social Services]].<ref name="NAA CA 32">{{citation|title=CA 32: Department of Social Services, Central Office|url=http://naa12.naa.gov.au/scripts/SearchOld.asp?Number=CA+32|publisher=National Archives of Australia|accessdate=24 April 2014}}</ref> Upon his retirement from the Social Services Department, Goodes was appointed a member of the Commonwealth Grants Commission.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://pmtranscripts.dpmc.gov.au/browse.php?did=1162|title=Commonwealth Grants Commission Statement|first=Robert|last=Menzies|author-link=Robert Menzies|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140424033412/http://pmtranscripts.dpmc.gov.au/browse.php?did=1162|date=30 September 1965|archivedate=24 April 2014}}</ref>

Goodes died on 12 July 1986.<ref name=CTObit/>

==Awards==
Goodes was made a Commander of the Order of the British Empire in January&nbsp;1960, for his service as Director-General of the Department of Social Services.<ref>{{citation|url=http://www.itsanhonour.gov.au/honours/honour_roll/search.cfm?aus_award_id=1064840&search_type=quick&showInd=true|archivedate=24 April 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140424025154/http://www.itsanhonour.gov.au/honours/honour_roll/search.cfm?aus_award_id=1064840&search_type=quick&showInd=true|title=Search Australian Honours: GOODES, Herbert John|publisher=Australian Government|work=itsanhonour.gov.au}}</ref>

